If you need help on running it, check the help by typing:

python simul.py --help

Examples:
---------

1) Run a strategy:
-----------------
python simul.py -f <input_file/graph> -o <output_file> -t <tbfc, tbf, rand, ...>  -n <#_rand_iteration>

2) Get efficiencies:
--------------------
python simul.py -f <file_in> -N <#_nodes> -M <#_links> -t eff-check 

3) Get theorical efficiencies:
-----------------------------
python simul.py -N 476 -M 4571 -t eff-spectral

4) Draw a graph with best and worst strat:
-----------------------------------------
python engine/draw.py -f <list of files>
